# Privacy Policy for "Thank God" Chrome Extension

**Last Updated: May 1, 2026**

Your privacy is our priority. This Privacy Policy explains how the "Thank God" Chrome extension handles your data.

### 1. Data Collection and Usage
The "Thank God" extension is designed to be **completely private and local**.
- **No Personal Data Collection**: We do not collect, store, or transmit any personal information, including names, email addresses, or browsing history.
- **Local Storage**: All user preferences (religion selection, theme choice, and favorites) are stored locally on your device using the `chrome.storage.sync` API. This data is only used to personalize your experience within the extension and is synced only with your own Google account if you are signed in.
- **No Tracking**: We do not use cookies, analytics, or any tracking scripts.

### 2. Permissions
The extension requests the following permissions for specific functionalities:
- **`storage`**: To save your preferences and favorite blessings locally.
- **`alarms`**: To schedule the optional daily morning reminder.
- **`notifications`**: To display the daily blessing reminder on your desktop.

### 3. Third-Party Services
The extension does not share any data with third-party services. All content (blessings and quotes) is bundled locally within the extension.

### 4. Security
We follow industry-standard best practices to ensure your local data is secure. Since no data is transmitted to our servers, your information remains under your control.

### 5. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be reflected by the "Last Updated" date at the top of this document.

### 6. Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us through the Chrome Web Store support page.

---
*By using the "Thank God" extension, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy.*
